#CarpalTunnelSyndrome Pressure on the nerve interferes with both sensory and motor function of the nerve
#CarpalTunnelSyndrome  associated w/ overuse of hand, pregnancy, #diabetes, rheumatoid arthritis, acromegaly, #amyloidosis, #hypothyroidism.
#CarpalTunnelSyndrome  pain in the hand affecting the palm, thumb, index finger, and the radial half of the ring finger
#CarpalTunnelSyndrome; Pain is worse at night
#CarpalTunnelSyndrome; Tinel sign: reproduction of pain and tingling with tapping or percussion of the median nerve
#CarpalTunnelSyndrome; Phalen sign: reproduction of symptoms with flexion of the wrists to 90 degrees
#CarpalTunnelSyndrome; Diagnostic Test: Simple compression of the nerve by squeezing it helps confirm diagnosis.
#CarpalTunnelSyndrome; The most accurate diagnostic tests are electromyography and nerve conduction testing.
#CarpalTunnelSyndrome; The best initial therapy is with wrist splints to immobilize the hand in a position to relieve pressure.
#CarpalTunnelSyndrome; Patients should avoid manual activity. Steroid injection is used if splints and NSAIDS do not control symptoms.
#CarpalTunnelSyndrome; Surgery can be curative by mechanically decompressing the tunnel such as with cutting open the flexor retinaculum.
